description: panda is a python package that provides fast flexible and expressive data structure designed to make working with relational or labeled data both easy and intuitive it aim to be the fundamental high level building block for doing practical real world data analysis in python additionally it ha the broader goal of becoming the most powerful and flexible open source data analysis manipulation tool available in any language it is already well on it way towards this goal here are just a few of the thing that panda doe well the source code is currently hosted on github at http github com panda dev pandasbinary installers for the latest released version are available at the python package index pypi and on conda see the full installation instruction for minimum supported version of required recommended and optional dependency to install panda from source you need cython in addition to the normal dependency above cython can be installed from pypi in the panda directory same one where you found this file after cloning the git repo execute or for installing in development mode if you have make you can also use make develop to run the same command or alternativelysee the full instruction for installing from source bsd the official documentation is hosted on pydata org http panda pydata org panda doc stablework on panda started at aqr a quantitative hedge fund in description: build http github com hpyproject hpy action workflow ci yml badge svg http github com hpyproject hpy action workflow ci yml documentation http readthedocs org project hpy badge http hpy readthedocs io irc channel hpy on libera chat http libera chat mailing list hpy dev python org http mail python org mailman list hpy dev python org the goal of the project is to design a better api for extending python in c the current api is specific to the current implementation of cpython it expose a lot of internal detail which make it hard to implement it for other python implementation e g pypy graalpython jython ironpython etc to experiment with new thing inside cpython itself e g using a gc instead of refcounting or to remove the gilthe goal of this project is to improve the situation by designing a new api which solves some of the current problem more specifically the goal include but are not necessarily limited to to be usable on cpython right now with no or almost no performance impactto make the adoption incremental it should be possible to migrate existing c extension piece by piece and to use the old and the new api side by side during the transitionto provide better debugging experience in debug mode you could get precise notification about which handle are kept open for too long or used after being closed to be more friendly for other implementation in particular we do not want reference counting to be part of the api we want a more generic way of managing resource which is possible to implement with different strategy including the existing reference counting and or with a moving gc like the one used by pypy or java for example to be smaller and easier to study use manage than the existing oneto avoid to expose internal detail of a specific implementation so that each implementation can experiment with new memory layout of object add optimization etc to be written in a way which could make it possible in the future to have a single binary which is abi compatible across multiple python version and or multiple implementationsinternal detail might still be available but in a opt in way for example if cython want to iterate over a list of integer it can ask if the implementation provides a direct low level access to the content e g in the form of a int t array and use that but at the same time be ready to handle the generic fallback case we will write a small c library which implement the new api on top of the existing one no change to cpython neededpypy will implement this natively extension using this api will be order of magnitude faster than the one using the existing old api see this blog post http www pypy org post inside cpyext why emulating cpython c html for detail cython will adopt this from day one existing cython program will benefit from this automaticallythe existing c api is becoming a problem for cpython and for the evolution of the language itself this project make it possible to make experiment which might be officially adopted in the futurefor pypy it will give obvious speed benefit for example data scientist will be able to get the benefit of fast c library and fast python code at the same time something which is hard to achieve nowthe current implementation is too tied to cpython and proved to be a problem for almost all the other alternative implementation having an api which is designed to work well on two different implementation will make the job much easier for future one going from to n is much easier than going from to arguably it will be easier to learn and understand than the massive cpython c apisee also python performance past present future http github com vstinner talk raw main europython python performance pdf by victor stinner the h in hpy stand for handle one of the key idea of the new api is to use fully opaque handle to represent and pas around python object become a financial contributor and help u sustain the hpy community contribute to hpy http opencollective com hpy contribute

description: the python sql toolkit and object relational mappersqlalchemy is the python sql toolkit and object relational mapper that give application developer the full power and flexibility of sql sqlalchemy provides a full suite of well known enterprise level persistence pattern designed for efficient and high performing database access adapted into a simple and pythonic domain language major sqlalchemy feature include an industrial strength orm built from the core on the identity map unit of work and data mapper pattern these pattern allow transparent persistence of object using a declarative configuration system domain model can be constructed and manipulated naturally and change are synchronized with the current transaction automatically a relationally oriented query system exposing the full range of sql s capability explicitly including join subqueries correlation and most everything else in term of the object model writing query with the orm us the same technique of relational composition you use when writing sql while you can drop into literal sql at any time it s virtually never needed a comprehensive and flexible system of eager loading for related collection and object collection are cached within a session and can be loaded on individual access all at once using join or by query per collection across the full result set a core sql construction system and dbapi interaction layer the sqlalchemy core is separate from the orm and is a full database abstraction layer in it own right and includes an extensible python based sql expression language schema metadata connection pooling type coercion and custom type all primary and foreign key constraint are assumed to be composite and natural surrogate integer primary key are of course still the norm but sqlalchemy never assumes or hardcodes to this model database introspection and generation database schema can be reflected in one step into python structure representing database metadata those same structure can then generate create statement right back out all within the core independent of the orm sqlalchemy s philosophy sql database behave le and le like object collection the more size and performance start to matter object collection behave le and le like table and row the more abstraction start to matter sqlalchemy aim to accommodate both of these principle an orm doesn t need to hide the r a relational database provides rich set based functionality that should be fully exposed sqlalchemy s orm provides an open ended set of pattern that allow a developer to construct a custom mediation layer between a domain model and a relational schema turning the so called object relational impedance issue into a distant memory the developer in all case make all decision regarding the design structure and naming convention of both the object model a well a the relational schema sqlalchemy only provides the mean to automate the execution of these decision with sqlalchemy there s no such thing a the orm generated a bad query you retain full control over the structure of query including how join are organized how subqueries and correlation is used what column are requested everything sqlalchemy doe is ultimately the result of a developer initiated decision don t use an orm if the problem doesn t need one sqlalchemy consists of a core and separate orm component the core offer a full sql expression language that allows pythonic construction of sql construct that render directly to sql string for a target database returning result set that are essentially enhanced dbapi cursor transaction should be the norm with sqlalchemy s orm nothing go to permanent storage until commit is called sqlalchemy encourages application to create a consistent mean of delineating the start and end of a series of operation never render a literal value in a sql statement bound parameter are used to the greatest degree possible allowing query optimizers to cache query plan effectively and making sql injection attack a non issue latest documentation is at http www sqlalchemy org doc full documentation for installation is at installation please refer to the sqlalchemy community guide above all sqlalchemy place great emphasis on polite thoughtful and constructive communication between user and developer please see our current code of conduct at code of conduct sqlalchemy is distributed under the mit license

description: werkzeug german noun tool etymology werk work zeug stuff werkzeug is a comprehensive wsgi web application library it began a a simple collection of various utility for wsgi application and ha become one of the most advanced wsgi utility library it includes an interactive debugger that allows inspecting stack trace and source code in the browser with an interactive interpreter for any frame in the stack a full featured request object with object to interact with header query args form data file and cooky a response object that can wrap other wsgi application and handle streaming data a routing system for matching url to endpoint and generating url for endpoint with an extensible system for capturing variable from url http utility to handle entity tag cache control date user agent cooky file and more a threaded wsgi server for use while developing application locally a test client for simulating http request during testing without requiring running a server werkzeug doesn t enforce any dependency it is up to the developer to choose a template engine database adapter and even how to handle request it can be used to build all sort of end user application such a blog wikis or bulletin board flask wrap werkzeug using it to handle the detail of wsgi while providing more structure and pattern for defining powerful application install and update using pip the pallet organization develops and support werkzeug and other popular package in order to grow the community of contributor and user and allow the maintainer to devote more time to the project please donate today documentation http werkzeug palletsprojects com change http werkzeug palletsprojects com change pypi release http pypi org project werkzeug source code http github com pallet werkzeug issue tracker http github com pallet werkzeug issue website http palletsprojects com p werkzeug twitter http twitter com palletsteamchat http discord gg pallet

description: an asgi web server for python documentation http www uvicorn orgrequirements python for python support install version uvicorn is an asgi web server implementation for python until recently python ha lacked a minimal low level server application interface for async framework the asgi specification fill this gap and mean we re now able to start building a common set of tooling usable across all async framework uvicorn support http and websockets install using pip this will install uvicorn with minimal pure python dependency this will install uvicorn with cython based dependency where possible and other optional extra in this context cython based mean the following moreover optional extra mean that create an application in example py run the server most well established python web framework started out a wsgi based framework wsgi application are a single synchronous callable that take a request and return a response this doesn t allow for long lived connection like you get with long poll http or websocket connection which wsgi doesn t support well having an async concurrency model also allows for option such a lightweight background task and can be le of a limiting factor for endpoint that have long period being blocked on network i o such a dealing with slow http request a strength of the asgi protocol is that it decouples the server implementation from the application framework this allows for an ecosystem of interoperating webservers and application framework the first asgi server implementation originally developed to power django channel is the daphne webserver it is run widely in production and support http http and websockets any of the example application given here can equally well be run using daphne instead hypercorn wa initially part of the quart web framework before being separated out into a standalone asgi server hypercorn support http http and websockets it also support the excellent trio async framework a an alternative to asyncio mangum is an adapter for using asgi application with aws lambda api gateway uvicorn is bsd licensed code designed crafted with care

description: portalocker is a library to provide an easy api to file locking an important detail to note is that on linux and unix system the lock are advisory by default by specifying the o mand option to the mount command it is possible to enable mandatory file locking on linux this is generally not recommended however for more information about the subject http en wikipedia org wiki file lockinghttp stackoverflow com question portalocker doe not seem to lockhttps stackoverflow com question mandatory file lock on linuxthe module is currently maintained by rick van hattem wolph wol ph the project resides at http github com wolph portalocker bug and feature request can be submitted there patch are also very welcome this library now feature a lock based on redis which allows for lock across multiple thread process and even distributed lock across multiple computer it is an extremely reliable redis lock that is based on pubsub a opposed to most redis locking system based on key value pair this locking method is based on the pubsub system the big advantage is that if the connection get killed due to network issue crashing process or otherwise it will still immediately unlock instead of waiting for a lock timeout first make sure you have everything installed correctly usage is really easy the api is essentially identical to the other lock class so in addition to the with statement you can also use lock acquire python wa supported in version before portalocker if you are still using python you can run this to install on some networked filesystems it might be needed to force a o fsync before closing the file so it s actually written before another client read the file effectively this come down to http portalocker readthedocs org en latest http github com wolph portalockerhttps github com wolph portalocker issueshttps pypi python org pypi portalockerhttp w wol ph to make sure your cache generation script don t race use the lock class to customize the opening and locking a manual approach is also possible explicitly unlocking is not needed in most case but omitting it ha been known to cause issue http github com azuread microsoft authentication extension for python issue issuecomment if needed it can be done through do note that your data might still be in a buffer so it is possible that your data is not available until you flush or close to create a cross platform bounded semaphore across multiple process you can use the boundedsemaphore class which function somewhat similar to threading boundedsemaphore more example can be found in the test this library follows semantic versioning every release ha a git tag with a commit message for the tag explaining what wa added and or changed the list of tag release including the commit message can be found here http github com wolph portalocker releasessee the license file

description: sacred is a tool to help you configure organize log and reproduce experiment it is designed to do all the tedious overhead work that you need to do around your actual experiment in order to keep track of all the parameter of your experimenteasily run your experiment for different settingssave configuration for individual run in a databasereproduce your resultssacred achieves this through the following main mechanism configscopes a very convenient way of the local variable in a function to define the parameter your experiment us config injection you can access all parameter of your configuration from every function they are automatically injected by name command line interface you get a powerful command line interface for each experiment that you can use to change parameter and run different variant observer sacred provides observer that log all kind of information about your experiment it dependency the configuration you used the machine it is run on and of course the result these can be saved to a mongodb for easy access later automatic seeding help controlling the randomness in your experiment such that the result remain reproducible script to train an svm on the iris datasetthe same script a a sacred experimentthe documentation is hosted at readthedocs you can directly install it from the python package index with pip pip install sacredor if you want to do it manually you can checkout the current version from git and install it yourself you might want to also install the numpy and the pymongo package they are optional dependency but they offer some cool feature pip install numpy pymongothe test for sacred use the pytest package you can execute them by running pytest in the sacred directory like this pytestthere is also a config file for tox so you can automatically run the test for various python version like this toxif you find a bug have a feature request or want to discus something general you are welcome to open an issue if you have a specific question related to the usage of sacred please ask a question on stackoverflow under the python sacred tag we value documentation a lot if you find something that should be included in the documentation please document it or let u know whats missing if you are using sacred in one of your project and want to share your code with others put your repo in the project using sacred doc project using sacred rst list pull request are highly welcome at this point there are three frontends to the database entry created by sacred that i m aware of they are developed externally a separate project omniboard is a web dashboard that help in visualizing the experiment and metric log collected by sacred omniboard is written with react node j express and bootstrap incense is a python library to retrieve run stored in a mongodb and interactively display metric and artifact in jupyter notebook sacredboard is a web based dashboard interface to the sacred run stored in a mongodb neptune is a web service that let you visualize organize and compare your experiment run once thing are logged to neptune you can share it with others add comment and even access object via experiment api in order to log your run to neptune all you need to do is add an observer for more info check the neptune contrib library sacredbrowser is a pyqt application to browse the mongodb entry created by sacred experiment feature include custom query sorting of the result access to the stored source code and many more no installation is required and it can connect to a local database or over the network prophet is an early prototype of a webinterface to the mongodb entry created by sacred experiment that is discontinued it requires you to run restheart to access the database sumatra take a different approach by providing commandline tool to initialize a project and then run arbitrary code not just python it track information about all run in a sql database and even provides a nice browser tool it integrates le tightly with the code to be run which make it easily applicable to non python experiment but that also mean it requires more setup for each experiment and configuration need to be done using file use this project if you need to run non python experiment or are ok with the additional setup configuration overhead similar to sumatra fglab is an external tool that can keep track of run from any program project are configured via a json schema and the program need to accept these configuration via command line option fglab also take the role of a basic scheduler by distributing run over several machine by tracing system call during program execution cde creates a snapshot of all used file and library to guarantee the ability to reproduce any unix program execution it only solves reproducibility but it doe so thoroughly this project is released under the term of the mit license k greff a klein m chovanec f hutter and j schmidhuber the sacred infrastructure for computational research in proceeding of the th python in science conference scipy austin texas pp

description: aiofiles is an apache licensed library written in python for handling local disk file in asyncio application ordinary local file io is blocking and cannot easily and portably made asynchronous this mean doing file io may interfere with asyncio application which shouldn t block the executing thread aiofiles help with this by introducing asynchronous version of file that support delegating operation to a separate thread pool asynchronous iteration is also supported asynchronous interface to tempfile module a file api very similar to python s standard blocking apisupport for buffered and unbuffered binary file and buffered text filessupport for async await pep constructsasync interface to tempfile moduleto install aiofiles simply file are opened using the aiofiles open coroutine which in addition to mirroring the builtin open accepts optional loop and executor argument if loop is absent the default loop will be used a per the set asyncio policy if executor is not specified the default event loop executor will be used in case of success an asynchronous file object is returned with an api identical to an ordinary file except the following method are coroutines and delegate to an executor closeflushisattyreadreadallread readintoreadlinereadlinesseekseekabletelltruncatewritablewritewritelinesin case of failure one of the usual exception will be raised the aiofiles o module contains executor enabled coroutine version of several useful o function that deal with file statsendfilerenamerenamesreplaceremoveunlinkmkdirmakedirsrmdirremovedirslinksymlinkreadlinklistdirscandirpath existspath isfilepath isdirpath islinkpath getsizepath getatimepath getctimepath samefilepath sameopenfileaiofiles tempfile implement the following interface temporaryfilenamedtemporaryfilespooledtemporaryfiletemporarydirectoryresults return wrapped with a context manager allowing use with async with and async for real file io can be mocked by patching aiofiles threadpool sync open a desired the return type also need to be registered with the aiofiles threadpool wrap dispatcher description: alembic is a database migration tool written by the author of sqlalchemy a migration tool offer the following functionality can emit alter statement to a database in order to change the structure of table and other constructsprovides a system whereby migration script may be constructed each script indicates a particular series of step that can upgrade a target database to a new version and optionally a series of step that can downgrade similarly doing the same step in reverse allows the script to execute in some sequential manner the goal of alembic are very open ended and transparent configuration and operation a new alembic environment is generated from a set of template which is selected among a set of option when setup first occurs the template then deposit a series of script that define fully how database connectivity is established and how migration script are invoked the migration script themselves are generated from a template within that series of script the script can then be further customized to define exactly how database will be interacted with and what structure new migration file should take full support for transactional ddl the default script ensure that all migration occur within a transaction for those database which support this postgresql microsoft sql server migration can be tested with no need to manually undo change upon failure minimalist script construction basic operation like renaming table column adding removing column changing column attribute can be performed through one line command like alter column rename table add constraint there is no need to recreate full sqlalchemy table structure for simple operation like these the function themselves generate minimalist schema structure behind the scene to achieve the given ddl sequence auto generation of migration while real world migration are far more complex than what can be automatically determined alembic can still eliminate the initial grunt work in generating new migration directive from an altered schema the autogenerate feature will inspect the current status of a database using sqlalchemy s schema inspection capability compare it to the current state of the database model a specified in python and generate a series of candidate migration rendering them into a new migration script a python directive the developer then edits the new file adding additional directive and data migration a needed to produce a finished migration table and column level change can be detected with constraint and index to follow a well full support for migration generated a sql script those of u who work in corporate environment know that direct access to ddl command on a production database is a rare privilege and dba want textual sql script alembic s usage model and command are oriented towards being able to run a series of migration into a textual output file a easily a it run them directly to a database care must be taken in this mode to not invoke other operation that rely upon in memory selects of row alembic try to provide helper construct like bulk insert to help with data oriented operation that are compatible with script based ddl non linear dependency graph versioning script are given uuid identifier similarly to a dvcs and the linkage of one script to the next is achieved via human editable marker within the script themselves the structure of a set of migration file is considered a a directed acyclic graph meaning any migration file can be dependent on any other arbitrary set of migration file or none at all through this open ended system migration file can be organized into branch multiple root and mergepoints without restriction command are provided to produce new branch root and merges of branch automatically provide a library of alter construct that can be used by any sqlalchemy application the ddl construct build upon sqlalchemy s own ddlelement base and can be used standalone by any application or script at long last bring sqlite and it inablity to alter thing into the fold but in such a way that sqlite s very special workflow need are accommodated in an explicit way that make the most of a bad situation through the concept of a batch migration where multiple change to a table can be batched together to form a series of instruction for a single subsequent move and copy workflow you can even use move and copy workflow for other database if you want to recreate a table in the background on a busy system documentation and status of alembic is at http alembic sqlalchemy org alembic is part of the sqlalchemy project and adheres to the same standard and convention a the core project please refer to the sqlalchemy community guide for guideline on coding and description: this document describes the source code for the eclipse paho mqtt python client library which implement version and of the mqtt protocol this code provides a client class which enable application to connect to an mqtt broker to publish message and to subscribe to topic and receive published message it also provides some helper function to make publishing one off message to an mqtt server very straightforward it support python or the mqtt protocol is a machine to machine m m internet of thing connectivity protocol designed a an extremely lightweight publish subscribe messaging transport it is useful for connection with remote location where a small code footprint is required and or network bandwidth is at a premium paho is an eclipse foundation project installationknown limitationsconstructor reinitialiseoption functionsconnect reconnect disconnectnetwork looppublishingsubscribe unsubscribecallbacksexternal event loop supportglobal helper functionssinglemultiplesimpleusing callbackreporting bugsmore informationthe latest stable version is available in the python package index pypi and can be installed usingor with virtualenv to obtain the full code including example and test you can clone the git repository once you have the code it can be installed from your repository a well to perform all test including mqtt v test you also need to clone paho mqtt testing in paho mqtt python folder the following are the known unimplemented mqtt feature when clean session is false the session is only stored in memory not persisted this mean that when client is restarted not just reconnected the object is recreated usually because the program wa restarted the session is lost this result in possible message lost the following part of client session is lost qos message which have been received from the server but have not been completely acknowledged since the client will blindly acknowledge any pubcomp last message of a qos transaction it won t hang but will lost this qos message qos and qos message which have been sent to the server but have not been completely acknowledged this mean that message passed to publish may be lost this could be mitigated by taking care that all message passed to publish ha a corresponding on publish call it also mean that the broker may have the qos message in the session since the client start with an empty session it don t know it and will re use the mid this is not yet fixed also when clean session is true this library will republish qos message accross network reconnection this mean that qos message won t be lost but the standard say that if we should discard any message for which the publish packet wa sent our choice mean that we are not compliant with the standard and it s possible for qos to be received twice you should you clean session false if you need the qos guarantee of only one delivery detailed api documentation is available through pydoc sample are available in the example directory the package provides two module a full client and a helper for simple publishing here is a very simple example that subscribes to the broker sys topic tree and print out the resulting message you can use the client class a an instance within a class or by subclassing the general usage flow is a follows create a client instanceconnect to a broker using one of the connect functionscall one of the loop function to maintain network traffic flow with the brokeruse subscribe to subscribe to a topic and receive messagesuse publish to publish message to the brokeruse disconnect to disconnect from the brokercallbacks will be called to allow the application to process event a necessary these callback are described below the client constructor take the following argument the unique client id string used when connecting to the broker if client id is zero length or none then one will be randomly generated in this case the clean session parameter must be true a boolean that determines the client type if true the broker will remove all information about this client when it disconnect if false the client is a durable client and subscription information and queued message will be retained when the client disconnect note that a client will never discard it own outgoing message on disconnect calling connect or reconnect will cause the message to be resent use reinitialise to reset a client to it original state user defined data of any type that is passed a the userdata parameter to callback it may be updated at a later point with the user data set function the version of the mqtt protocol to use for this client can be either mqttv mqttv or mqttv set to websockets to send mqtt over websockets leave at the default of tcp to use raw tcp the reinitialise function reset the client to it starting state a if it had just been created it take the same argument a the client constructor these function represent option that can be set on the client to modify it behaviour in the majority of case this must be done before connecting to a broker set the maximum number of message with qos that can be part way through their network flow at once default to increasing this value will consume more memory but can increase throughput set the maximum number of outgoing message with qos that can be pending in the outgoing message queue default to mean unlimited but due to implementation currently limited to message in queue in flight when the queue is full any further outgoing message would be dropped set the time in second before a message with qos is retried if the broker doe not respond this is set to second by default and should not normally need changing set websocket connection option these option will only be used if transport websockets wa passed into the client constructor the mqtt path to use on the broker either a dictionary specifying a list of extra header which should be appended to the standard websocket header or a callable that take the normal websocket header and return a new dictionary with a set of header to connect to the broker must be called before connect an example of how this can be used with the aws iot platform is in the example folder configure network encryption and authentication option enables ssl tl support a string path to the certificate authority certificate file that are to be treated a trusted by this client if this is the only option given then the client will operate in a similar manner to a web browser that is to say it will require the broker to have a certificate signed by the certificate authority in ca cert and will communicate using tl v but will not attempt any form of authentication this provides basic network encryption but may not be sufficient depending on how the broker is configured by default on python or the default certification authority of the system is used on older python version this parameter is mandatory string pointing to the pem encoded client certificate and private key respectively if these argument are not none then they will be used a client information for tl based authentication support for this feature is broker dependent note that if either of these file in encrypted and need a password to decrypt it python will ask for the password at the command line it is not currently possible to define a callback to provide the password defines the certificate requirement that the client imposes on the broker by default this is ssl cert required which mean that the broker must provide a certificate see the ssl pydoc for more information on this parameter specifies the version of the ssl tl protocol to be used by default if the python version support it the highest tl version is detected if unavailable tl v is used previous version all version beginning with ssl are possible but not recommended due to possible security problem a string specifying which encryption cipher are allowable for this connection or none module documentation section about security consideration for more information must be called before connect configure verification of the server hostname in the server certificate if value is set to true it is impossible to guarantee that the host you are connecting to is not impersonating your server this can be useful in initial server testing but make it possible for a malicious third party to impersonate your server through dns spoofing for example do not use this function in a real system setting value to true mean there is no point using encryption must be called before connect and after tl set or tl set context enable logging using the standard python logging package see pep this may be used at the same time a the on log callback method if logger is specified then that logging logger delay second it s doubled between subsequent attempt up to max delay the delay is reset to min delay when the connection complete e g the connack is received not just the tcp connection is established the connect function connects the client to a broker this is a blocking function it take the following argument the hostname or ip address of the remote brokerthe network port of the server host to connect to default to note that the default port for mqtt over ssl tl is so if you are using tl set or tl set context the port may need providing manuallymaximum period in second allowed between the documentation for how to enable credential ed request and please make sure you add some sort of csrf protection before doing so install the extension with using pip or easy install this package expose a flask extension which by default enables cors support on all route for all origin and method it allows parameterization of all cors header on a per resource level the package also contains a decorator for those who prefer this approach in the simplest case initialize the flask cors extension with default argument in order to allow cors for all domain on all route see the full list of option in the documentation alternatively you can specify cors option on a resource and origin level of granularity by passing a dictionary a the resource option mapping path to a set of option see the full list of option in the documentation this extension also expose a simple decorator to decorate flask route with simply add cross origin below a call to flask s app route to allow cors on a given route see the full list of option in the decorator documentation for a full list of option please see the full documentationif thing aren t working a you expect enable logging to help understand what is going on under the hood and why a simple set of test is included in test to run install nose and simply invoke nosetests or python setup py test to exercise the test question comment or improvement please create an issue on github tweet at corydolphin or send me an email i do my best to include every contribution proposed in any way that i can this flask extension is based upon the decorator for the http access control written by armin ronacher

zone message name and record to see a few of the way dnspython can be used look in the example directory dnspython is a utility to work with dns etc host is thus not used for simple forward dns lookup it s better to use socket getaddrinfo or socket gethostbyname dnspython originated at nominum where it wa developed to facilitate the testing of dns software this is dnspython please read what s new for information about the change in this release dnspython s default installation doe not depend on any module other than those in the python standard library to use some feature additional module must be installed for convenience pip option are defined for the requirement if you want to use dns over http run pip install dnspython doh if you want to use dnssec functionality run pip install dnspython dnssec if you want to use internationalized domain name idna functionality you must run pip install dnspython idna if you want to use the trio asynchronous i o package run pip install dnspython trio if you want to use the curio asynchronous i o package run pip install dnspython curio if you want to use wmi on window to determine the active dns setting instead of the default registry scanning method run pip install dnspython wmi note that you can install any combination of the above e g pip install dnspython doh dnssec idna python x support ended with the release of dnspython through x support python and later a of dnspython the minimum supported python version will be we plan to align future support with the lifetime of the python version documentation ha moved to dnspython readthedocs io the changelog ha been discontinued please see the github project page and git history for detailed change information

description: python helper to limit the number of thread used in the threadpool backed of common native library used for scientific computing and data science e g blas and openmp fine control of the underlying thread pool size can be useful in workload that involve nested parallelism so a to mitigate oversubscription issue for user install the last published version from pypi for contributor install from the source repository in developer mode then you run the test with pytest get a json description of thread pool initialized when importing python package such a numpy or scipy for instance the json information is written on stdout if some of the package are missing a warning message is displayed on stderr introspect the current state of the threadpool enabled runtime library that are loaded when importing python package in the above example numpy wa installed from the default anaconda channel and come with mkl and it intel openmp libiomp implementation while xgboost wa installed from pypi org and link against gnu openmp libgomp so both openmp runtimes are loaded in the same python program the state of these library is also accessible through the object oriented api control the number of thread used by the underlying runtime library in specific section of your python program the threadpools can also be controlled via the object oriented api which is especially useful to avoid searching through all the loaded shared library each time it will however not act on library loaded after the instantiation of the threadpoolcontroller threadpool limit and threadpoolcontroller can also be used a decorator to set the maximum number of thread used by the supported library at a function level the decorator are accessible through their wrap method when one want to have sequential blas call within an openmp parallel region it s safer to set limit sequential blas under openmp since setting limit and user api blas might not lead to the expected behavior in some configuration e g openblas with the openmp threading layer http github com xianyi openblas issue threadpool limit can fail to limit the number of inner thread when nesting parallel loop managed by distinct openmp runtime implementation for instance libgomp from gcc and libomp from clang llvm or libiomp from icc see the test openmp nesting function in test test threadpoolctl py for an example more information can be found at http github com jeremiedbb nested openmpnote however that this problem doe not happen when threadpool limit is used to limit the number of thread used internally by blas call that are themselves nested under openmp parallel loop threadpool limit work a expected even if the inner blas implementation relies on a distinct openmp implementation using intel openmp icc and llvm openmp clang in the same python program under linux is known to cause problem see the following guide for more detail and workarounds http github com joblib threadpoolctl blob master multiple openmp mdsetting the maximum number of thread of the openmp and blas library ha a global effect and impact the whole python process there is no thread level isolation a these library do not offer thread local apis to configure the number of thread to use in nested parallel call to make a release bump the version number version in threadpoolctl py build the distribution archive check the content of dist if everything is fine make a commit for the release tag it push the tag to github and then the initial dynamic library introspection code wa written by anton malakhov for the smp package available at http github com intelpython smp threadpoolctl extends this for other operating system contrary to smp threadpoolctl doe not attempt to limit the size of python multiprocessing pool thread or process or set operating system level cpu affinity constraint threadpoolctl only interacts with native library via their public runtime apis

application pika try to stay compatible with all of these and to make adapting it to a new environment a simple a possible pika s documentation can be found at http pika readthedocs io here is the most simple example of use sending a message with the pika blockingconnection adapter and an example of writing a blocking consumer pika adapter asyncio connection asyncioconnection asynchronous after connection attempt using all of the given connection parameter fail with non blocking adapter such a pika selectconnection and pika adapter asyncio connection asyncioconnection you can request a connection using multiple connection parameter instance via the connection adapter s create connection class method the single threaded usage constraint of an individual pika connection adapter instance may result in a dropped amqp stream connection due to amqp heartbeat timeout in consumer that take a long time to process an incoming message a common solution is to delegate processing of the incoming message to another thread while the connection adapter s thread continues to service it i o loop s message pump permitting amqp heartbeat and other i o to be serviced in a timely fashion message processed in another thread may not be acknowledged directly from that thread since all access to the connection adapter instance must be from a single thread which is the thread running the adapter s i o loop this is accomplished by requesting a callback to be executed in the adapter s i o loop thread for example the callback function s implementation might look like this the code running in the other thread may request the ack message function to be executed in the connection adapter s i o loop thread using an adapter specific mechanism pika blockingconnection abstract it i o loop from the application and thus expose pika blockingconnection add callback threadsafe refer to this method s docstring for additional information for example when using a non blocking connection adapter such a pika adapter asyncio connection asyncioconnection or pika selectconnection you use the underlying asynchronous framework s native api for requesting an i o loop bound callback from another thread for example pika selectconnection s i o loop provides add callback threadsafe pika adapter tornado connection tornadoconnection s i o loop ha add callback while pika adapter asyncio connection asyncioconnection s i o loop expose call soon threadsafe this threadsafe callback request mechanism may also be used to delegate publishing of message etc from a background thread to the connection adapter s thread some rabbitmq client bunny java net objective c swift provide a way to automatically recover connection it channel and topology e g queue binding and consumer after a network failure others require connection recovery to be performed by the application code and strive to make it a straightforward process pika fall into the second category pika support multiple connection adapter they take different approach to connection recovery for pika blockingconnection adapter exception handling can be used to check for connection error here is a very basic example description: waitress is a production quality pure python wsgi server with very acceptable performance it ha no dependency except one which live in the python standard library it run on cpython on doc pylonsproject org project waitress en latest when expose tracebacks is enabled waitress would fail to properly encode unicode thereby causing another error during error handling see http github com pylon waitress pull header length checking had a calculation that wa done incorrectly when the data wa received across multple socket read this calculation ha been corrected and no longer will waitress send back a request entity too large see http github com pylon waitress pull in a new feature wa introduced that allowed the wsgi thread to start sending data to the socket however this introduced a race condition whereby a socket may be closed in the sending thread while the main thread is about to call select therey causing the entire application to be taken down waitress will no longer close the socket in the wsgi thread instead waking up the main thread to cleanup see http github com pylon waitress pull security bugfixwaitress now validates that chunked encoding extension are valid and don t contain invalid character that are not allowed they are still skipped not processed but if they contain invalid data we no longer continue in and return a bad request this stop potential http desync http request smuggling thanks to zhang zeyu for reporting this issue see http github com pylon waitress security advisory ghsa f p jc c waitress now validates that the chunk length is only valid hex digit when parsing chunked encoding and value such a x and are no longer supported this stop potential http desync http request smuggling thanks to zhang zeyu for reporting this issue see http github com pylon waitress security advisory ghsa f p jc c waitress now validates that the content length sent by a remote contains only digit in accordance with rfc and will return a bad request when the content length header contains invalid data such a which would previously get parsed a and accepted this stop potential http desync http request smuggling thanks to zhang zeyu led to potential for random memory spike memory issue see http github com pylon waitress pull and http github com pylon waitress issue with thanks to florian schulze for testing vaidating this fix when the wsgi app start sending data to the output buffer we now attempt to send data directly to the socket this avoids needing to wake up the main thread to start sending data allowing faster request uri in nginx it is a string that contains the request path before separating the query string and decoding escaped character

description: this slackclient pypi project is in maintenance mode now and slack sdk project is the successor the v sdk provides more functionality such a socket mode oauth flow module scim api audit log api better asyncio support retry handler and many more refer to the migration guide to learn how to smoothly migrate your existing code the python slackclient library is a developer kit for interfacing with the slack web api and real time messaging rtm api on python and above comprehensive documentation on using the slack python can be found at http slack dev python slackclient whether you re building a custom app for your team or integrating a third party service into your slack workflow slack developer kit for python allows you to leverage the flexibility of python to get your project up and running a quickly a possible the python slackclient allows interaction with if you want to use our event api and interactivity feature please check the bolt for python bolt python library detail on the token and authentication can be found in our auth guide detail on the token and authentication can be found in our auth guide this library requires python and above if you require python please use our slackclient v x if you re unsure how to check what version of python you re on you can check it using the following note you may need to use python before your command to ensure you use the correct python path e g python versionwe recommend using pypi to install the slack developer kit for python we ve created this tutorial to build a basic slack app in le than minute it requires some general programming knowledge and python basic it focus on the interacting with slack s web and rtm api use it to give you an idea of how to use this sdk read the tutorial to get started slack provide a web api that give you the ability to build application that interact with slack in a variety of way this development kit is a module based wrapper that make interaction with that api easier we have a basic example here with some of the more common us but a full list of the available method are available here more detailed example can be found in our basic usage guide one of the most common use case is sending a message to slack if you want to send a message a your app or a a user this method can do both in our example we specify the channel name however it is recommended to use the channel id where possible also if your app s bot user is not in a channel yet invite the bot user before running the code snippet or add chat write public to bot token scope for posting in any public channel here we also ensure that the response back from slack is a successful one and that the message is the one we sent by using the assert statement we ve changed the process for uploading file to slack to be much easier and straight forward you can now just include a path to the file directly in the api call and upload it that way you can find the detail on this api call herethe real time messaging rtm api is a websocket based api that allows you to receive event from slack in real time and send message a user if you prefer event to be pushed to you instead we recommend using the http based event api instead most event type supported by the rtm api are also available in the event api you can check out our python slack event adaptor if you want to use this api instead an rtmclient allows apps to communicate with the slack platform s rtm api the event driven architecture of this client allows you to simply link callback to their corresponding event when an event occurs this client executes your callback while passing along any information it receives we also give you the ability to call our web client from inside your callback in our example below we watch for a message event that contains hello and if it received we call the say hello function we then issue a call to the web client to post back to the channel saying hi to the user please note that the default way of creating slack apps no longer support rtm api event using the rtm api must use a classic slack app with a plain bot scope if you already have a classic slack app you can use those credential if you don t and need to use the rtm api you can create a classic slack app from this link you can learn more in the api documentation also even if the slack app configuration page encourage you to upgrade to the newer permission model don t upgrade it and keep using the classic bot permission slackclient v and higher us aiohttp under the hood for asynchronous request and urllib for synchronous request normal usage of the library doe not run it in async hence a kwarg of run async true is needed when in async mode it important to remember to await or run run until complete the call if you are using a framework invoking the asyncio event loop like sanic jupyter notebook etc you can provide a custom ssl context or disable verification by passing the ssl option supported by both the rtm and the web client for async request see the aiohttp ssl documentation for sync request see the urllib ssl documentation a proxy is supported when making async request pas the proxy option supported by both the rtm and the web client for async request see aiohttp proxy documentation for sync request setting either http proxy env variable or the proxy option work using the async client and looking for a performance boost installing the optional dependency aiodns may help speed up dns resolving by the client we ve included it a an extra called optional if you re migrating from v x of slackclient to v x please follow our migration guide to ensure your app continues working after updating check out the migration guide here we no longer provide support for v or v of this sdk and only maintain the latest v version if you would like support from this project s maintainer please consider updating to the latest version of the sdk first otherwise you may visit the slack community for getting help using slack developer kit for python or just generally bond with your fellow slack developer

description: sagemaker python sdk is an open source library for training and deploying machine learning model on amazon sagemaker with the sdk you can train and deploy model using popular deep learning framework apache mxnet and tensorflow you can also train and deploy model with amazon algorithm which are scalable implementation of core machine learning algorithm that are optimized for learning estimatorssagemaker sparkml servingamazon sagemaker built in algorithm estimatorsusing sagemaker algorithmestimatorsconsuming sagemaker model packagesbyo docker container with sagemaker pip install command in the root directory of the repository sagemaker python sdk support unix linux and mac sagemaker python sdk is tested on python python python python a a managed service amazon sagemaker performs operation on your behalf on the aws hardware that is managed by amazon sagemaker amazon sagemaker can perform only operation that the user permit you can read more about which permission are necessary in the aws documentation the sagemaker python sdk should not require any additional permission aside from what is required for using sagemaker however if you are using an iam role with a path in it you should grant permission for iam getrole sagemaker python sdk is licensed under the apache license it is copyright amazon com inc or it affiliate all right reserved the license is available at http aws amazon com apache sagemaker python sdk ha unit test and integration test you can install the library needed to run the test by running pip install upgrade test or for zsh user pip install upgrade test unit testswe run unit test with tox which is a program that let you run unit test for multiple python version and also make sure the code fit our style guideline we run tox with all of our supported python version so to run unit test with the same configuration we do you need to have interpreter for those python version installed to run the unit test with tox run integration teststo run the integration test the following prerequisite must be metaws account credential are available in the environment for the boto client to use the aws account ha an iam role named sagemakerrole it should have the amazonsagemakerfullaccess policy attached a well a a policy with the necessary permission to use elastic inference we recommend selectively running just those integration test you d like to run you can filter by individual test function name with you can also run all of the integration test by running the following command which run them in sequence which may take a while you can also run them in parallel to enable all git hook in the githooks directory run these command in the repository directory to enable an individual git hook simply move it from the githooks directory to the git hook directory setup a python environment and install the dependency listed in doc requirement txt clone fork the repo and install your local version then cd into the sagemaker python sdk doc directory and run you can edit the template for any of the page in the doc by editing the rst file in the doc directory and then running make html again preview the site with a python web server view the website by visiting http localhost with sagemaker sparkml serving you can now perform prediction against a sparkml model in sagemaker in order to host a sparkml model in an instance of sparkmlmodel class and use deploy method to create an endpoint which can be used to perform prediction against your trained sparkml model once the model is deployed we can invoke the endpoint with a csv payload like this for more information about the different content type and accept format a well a the structure of the schema that sagemaker sparkml serving recognizes please see sagemaker sparkml serving container

description: python wrapper for the arxiv api arxiv is a project by the cornell university library that provides open access to article in physic mathematics computer science quantitative biology quantitative finance and statistic in your python script include the linea search specifies a search of arxiv s database to fetch arxiv record matching a search use search result or client result search to get a generator yielding result print the title fo the most recent article related to the keyword quantum fetch and print the title of the paper with id v the result object yielded by search result include metadata about each paper and some helper function for downloading their content the meaning of the underlying raw data is documented in the arxiv api user manual detail of atom result returned they also expose helper method for downloading paper result download pdf and result download source to download a pdf of the paper with id v run a search and then use result download pdf the same interface is available for downloading tar gz file of the paper source a client specifies a strategy for fetching result from arxiv s api it obscures pagination and retry logic for most use case the default client should suffice you can construct it explicitly with arxiv client or use it via the search result method search result us the default client setting if you want to use a client you ve defined instead of the default use client result to inspect this package s network behavior and api logic configure an info level logger

json to your system dic then specify your sudachi json with the r option ref setuptools rustrun build and test sh to run the test sudachi and sudachipy are developed by wap tokushima laboratory of ai description: the official python client for prometheus one install the client two paste the following into a python interpreter three visit http localhost to view the metric from one easy to use decorator you get prometheus s rate function allows calculation of both request per second and latency over time from this data in addition if you re on linux the process metric expose cpu memory and other information about the process for free this package can be found on pypi four type of metric are offered counter gauge summary and histogram see the documentation on metric type and instrumentation best practice on how to use them counter go up and reset when the process restarts if there is a suffix of total on the metric name it will be removed when exposing the time series for counter a total suffix will be added this is for compatibility between openmetrics and the prometheus text format a openmetrics requires the total suffix there are utility to count exception raised gauge can go up and down there are utility for common use case a gauge can also take it value from a callback summary track the size and number of event there are utility for timing code the python client doesn t store or expose quantile information at this time histogram track the size and number of event in bucket this allows for aggregatable calculation of quantiles the default bucket are intended to cover a typical web rpc request from millisecond to second they can be overridden by passing bucket keyword argument to histogram there are utility for timing code info track key value information usually about a whole target enum track which of a set of state something is currently in all metric can have label allowing grouping of related time series see the best practice on naming and label taking a counter a an example label can also be passed a keyword argument metric with label are not initialized when declared because the client can t know what value the label can have it is recommended to initialize the label value by calling the label method alone exemplar can be added to counter and histogram metric exemplar can be specified by passing a dict of label value pair to be exposed a the exemplar for example with a counter and with a histogram by default counter histogram and summary export an additional series suffixed with created and a value of the unix timestamp for when the metric wa created if this information is not helpful it can be disabled by setting the environment variable prometheus disable created series true the python client automatically export metric about process cpu usage ram file descriptor and start time these all have the prefix process and are only currently available on linux the namespace and pid constructor argument allows for exporting metric about other process for example the client also automatically export some metadata about python if using jython metadata about the jvm in use is also included this information is available a label on the python info metric the value of the metric is since it is the label that carry information by default the collected process gc and platform collector metric are exported if this information is not helpful it can be disabled using the following there are several option for exporting metric metric are usually exposed over http to be read by the prometheus server the easiest way to do this is via start http server which will start a http server in a daemon thread on the given port visit http localhost to view the metric to add prometheus exposition to an existing http server see the metricshandler class which provides a basehttprequesthandler it also serf a a simple example of how to write a custom endpoint to use prometheus with twisted there is metricsresource which expose metric a a twisted resource to use prometheus with wsgi there is make wsgi app which creates a wsgi application such an application can be useful when integrating prometheus metric with wsgi apps the method start wsgi server can be used to serve the metric through the wsgi reference implementation in a new thread by default the wsgi application will respect accept encoding gzip header used by prometheus and compress the response if such a header is present this behaviour can be disabled by passing disable compression true when creating the app like this to use prometheus with asgi there is make asgi app which creates an asgi application such an application can be useful when integrating prometheus metric with asgi apps by default the wsgi application will respect accept encoding gzip header used by prometheus and compress the response if such a header is present this behaviour can be disabled by passing disable compression true when creating the app like this to use prometheus with flask we need to serve metric through a prometheus wsgi application this can be achieved using flask s application dispatching below is a working example save the snippet below in a myapp py filerun the example web application like thisvisit http localhost metric to see the metricsthe textfile collector allows machine level statistic to be exported out via the node exporter this is useful for monitoring cronjobs or for writing cronjobs to expose metric about a machine system that the node exporter doe not support or would not make sense to perform at every scrape for example anything involving subprocesses a separate registry is used a the default registry may contain other metric such a those from the process collector the pushgateway allows ephemeral and batch job to expose their metric to prometheus a separate registry is used a the default registry may contain other metric such a those from the process collector pushgateway function take a grouping key push to gateway replaces metric with the same grouping key pushadd to gateway only replaces metric with the same name and grouping key and delete from gateway deletes metric with the given job and grouping key see the pushgateway documentation for more information instance ip grouping key return a grouping key with the instance label set to the host s ip address if the push gateway you are connecting to is protected with http basic auth you can use a special handler to set the authorization header tl auth is also supported when using the push gateway with a special handler it is also possible to expose metric to system other than prometheus this allows you to take advantage of prometheus instrumentation even if you are not quite ready to fully transition to prometheus yet metric are pushed over tcp in the graphite plaintext format graphite tag are also supported sometimes it is not possible to directly instrument code a it is not in your control this requires you to proxy metric from other system to do so you need to create a custom collector for example summarymetricfamily histogrammetricfamily and infometricfamily work similarly a collector may implement a describe method which return metric in the same format a collect though you don t have to include the sample this is used to predetermine the name of time series a collectorregistry expose and thus to detect collision and duplicate registration usually custom collector do not have to implement describe if describe is not implemented and the collectorregistry wa created with auto describe true which is the case for the default registry then collect will be called at registration time instead of describe if this could cause problem either implement a proper describe or if that s not practical have describe return an empty list prometheus client library presume a threaded model where metric are shared across worker this doesn t work so well for language such a python where it s common to have process rather than thread to handle large workload to handle this the client library can be put in multiprocess mode this come with a number of limitation there s several step to getting this working deployment the prometheus multiproc dir environment variable must be set to a directory that the client library can use for metric this directory must be wiped between process gunicorn run before startup is recommended this environment variable should be set from a start up shell script and not directly from python otherwise it may not propagate to child process metric collector the application must initialize a new collectorregistry and store the multi process collector inside it is a best practice to create this registry inside the context of a request to avoid metric registering themselves to a collector used by a multiprocesscollector if a registry with metric registered is used by a multiprocesscollector duplicate metric may be exported one for multiprocess and one for the process serving the request gunicorn configuration the gunicorn configuration file need to include the following function metric tuning gauge when gauge are used in multiprocess application you must decide how to handle the metric reported by each process gauge have several mode they can run in which can be selected with the multiprocess mode parameter prepend live to the beginning of the mode to return the same result but only considering living process e g liveall livesum livemax livemin the python client support parsing the prometheus text format this is intended for advanced use case where you have server exposing prometheus metric and need to get them into some other system

framework below is a simple example test case for testing login to some system you can find more example with link to related demo project from http robotframework org test or task are executed from
